## 4. The "Hand Feel" Experience

* Impact Sensation
    * Hardness Words: Dense, solid, unyielding on soft touches, crisp on hard impacts.
    * Feedback: Very direct and clear. You know exactly where on the racket the ball made contact.
    * Hold vs. Release: Short hold on passive shots; deep hold and explosive release on full-power drives.
    * Dwell Time: Moderate. Dependent entirely on the player's ability to sink the ball into the hard sponge.

* Sound/Click
    * Produces a sharp, cracking sound on maximum-effort shots, though it lacks the constant "click" of 47.5-degree or softer ESN rubbers.

