## 5. Compatibility & Setup Guide

* Best Blade Matches
    * Outer Carbon: Excellent for aggressive loopers wanting maximum speed and direct feel (e.g., Viscaria, Xiom Hugo HAL).
    * Inner Carbon: The ideal pairing. The softer wood feel balances the hard 52.5 sponge, increasing dwell time for heavy spin (e.g., Ovtcharov Innerforce, Xiom An Jaehyun).
    * All-Wood: Only recommended for very stiff 7-ply woods (e.g., Clipper Wood); 5-ply woods may feel too sluggish.
    * Mismatch Cases: Ultra-stiff, thick carbon blades paired with beginners will result in a complete loss of control.

* Forehand vs. Backhand Recommendation
    * Forehand: Highly recommended. The hardness and power perfectly suit the mechanics of a modern forehand stroke.
    * Backhand: Only for advanced players with exceptionally fast, compact backhand strokes.

* 40+ ABS Ball Suitability
    * Perfect match. The high grip and dense sponge counteract the loss of spin and speed inherent to the ABS plastic ball.

