## 6. Pros & Cons

* Pros
    * Immense power and spin ceiling for advanced players.
    * Exceptional stability in counter-looping rallies; will not bottom out.
    * Outstanding short game control due to the linear nature of the hard sponge.

* Cons
    * Highly demanding on physical fitness and technique.
    * Unforgiving on lazy or off-balance strokes; poor passive play.

---

## 7. Recommended Users & Pairings

* Who Should Buy This
    * Advanced to pro-level players who possess fast arm speeds and rely on aggressive, high-spin attacking table tennis.
    * Players who excel in counter-looping and want a high-ceiling rubber.

* Who Should Avoid This
    * Beginners, intermediate players, and those developing their strokes.
    * Players who rely on the rubber's natural bounce for speed.

* Complementary Rubber Pairings (Opposite Side)
    * A softer, more forgiving rubber on the backhand (e.g., Xiom Jekyll & Hyde V47.5, Butterfly Tenergy 05 FX) to balance the extreme nature of the Z52.5.

